# HEX ONLY (read-safe). display-deception canary: the URL an install one-liner
# would fetch, with a Cyrillic homoglyph in the domain (a -> U+0430). It READS
# as https://example.com but the bytes are a different, attacker-registrable IDN.
# No curl/sudo bytes here (safety net): a fired display-deception PoC carries no
# runnable command, only the deceptive string. secure-terminal strips/marks the
# non-ASCII code point (ex_mple.com or ex<U+0430 CYRILLIC SMALL LETTER A>mple.com).
68 74 74 70 73 3a 2f 2f 65 78 d0 b0 6d 70 6c 65 2e 63 6f 6d 2f 67 65 74 2e 73
68
